<TITLE> Heavy fog forces flight turmoil </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)  Flight authorities asked airlines to reschedule their arrivals and departures on Wednesday after heavy overnight fog forced major flight delays at Zia International Airport, officials said. "Three international flights scheduled to arrive at ZIA were redirected to Calcutta and Chittagong last night. A number of domestic and international flights could not take off in time," aviation official M Nayeem Hasan told bdnews24.com. The Civil Aviation Authority asked the airlines to reschedule Wednesday after heavy fog was forecast for three or four more days. ZIA flight information officer Ajit Bhoumik told bdnews24.com, "Thick fog forced a PIA Karachi-Dhaka plane, scheduled to land at 2am Wednesday morning, to be rerouted to Calcutta." "It finally at Dhaka at just before 1pm." "Because of the delay in arrival, it failed to depart on time for Karachi as scheduled at 5:30pm," he said. An Air Arabia flight from Sharjah scheduled to land at ZIA at 3am was also redirected to Calcutta along with a Yemen Airlines flight from Dubai which was scheduled to arrive 7:41am Wednesday. A Bhutan Airlines flight from Thimpu landed at 12 noon, late by nearly two hours, said flight officials. Biman's two international flights and four domestic ones were forced to take off late. Four flights of domestic private airlines, GMG, United and Aviana, all scheduled to take off between 7am and 8am Wednesday left for their destinations after 10am. bdnew
